To make this precise, we can use the fact that `Real.sinh(y) = y + y^3/3! + ...`. So `Real.sinh(r * x) = r * x + (r * x)^3/3! + ...`. Then `f(x) = (r * x + (r * x)^3/3! + ...)/x = r + r^3 * x^2/3! + ...`. As `x` approaches `0`, the terms with `x` in them go to `0`, so `f(x)` approaches `r`.

